    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The x^n example is the canonical counterexample in every analysis course. Our numerical evaluation shows pointwise convergence (each x^n &rarr; 0 for x &lt; 1), but the lack of uniform convergence is a theoretical fact about the supremum, not something a finite computation proves.</p>

